 & Out of Work advances its readers' grasp of the complexities of historical time in contemporary culture, moving the study of temporality forward in film and media studies, literary studies, critical theory, and cultural critique.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aUnemployed in literature. 0aWorking class in literature. 0aWorking class in motion pictures. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aIron Council.  aThe Fantastic Mr. Fox.  aThe Invention of Hugo Cabret.  aWreck-It Ralph.  aanimation.  afilm.  alabor.  aliterature.  aobsolescence.  aobsolete.  aproduction.  atechnology.  awork.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066608340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813597157zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813597157423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813597157.jpg  a978-3-11-066608-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK